[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring coverage issues**\n\nI'm considering coverage with a source line instead of \"Unknown,\" since there might be many false positives for generated tests. I wonder if the dynamic report after javaTest is needed. Existing tests for the private key might not have covered everything, as they use method handles instead of public ones. I'm pondering if the dynamic agent fails to see calls made by JDK serialization through reflection. I should inspect the compiled test to understand this better.\n\n**Examining serialization filters**\n\nI’m exploring whether BigInteger serialization might be excluded by a user filter. If TrackedBigInteger from the test package is filtered out, then that could be an issue too. I'm thinking I need to have objects in the org.bouncycastle package, but I can’t actually put tests there. Maybe I can use existing Bouncy Castle classes as serializable field values? However, defining a new class in that package isn't allowed. I wonder if the filter is only for target classes? This needs more thought!\n\n**Investigating coverage and subclasses**\n\nIt seems the coverage might include output from the Graal agent if the serialized class matches the filter. However, I can't achieve this with BigInteger unless I subclass it within the org.bouncycastle package. I can't put tests directly in the same package just to access package-private/internal elements, but I’m wondering if I can create a helper class in org.bouncycastle. I'll need to keep tests outside of library packages, but this does require some careful consideration.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0b73063cb9f920ab0169fc1f930af481958b813be85e0966d3\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp_B-eUQj9F0OMYHJmA6mmvKedwB4kfjtHV1_NzL_un6iRQZ6FgZ3TVlJpIG6EeW6XJ4lY7sCDbbAK-AoBxQziM1bl9mGJ8F6TVQ_JfqxrvpFr64Ve3Ry0-dMj8wkeEcBjd6iPHVCJyGPyR-kmUwhy2sE4rVd8Peo0ZVk2ZPPZcRj4VZc