ectedY);\n        assertThat(parameters).isNotNull();\n        assertThat(parameters.getP()).isEqualTo(expectedP);\n        assertThat(parameters.getQ()).isEqualTo(expectedQ);\n        assertThat(parameters.getG()).isEqualTo(expectedG);\n    }\n\n    private static void invokeReadObject(JDKDSAPublicKey publicKey, ObjectInputStream inputStream) throws Throwable {\n        READ_OBJECT.invokeExact(publicKey, inputStream);\n    }\n\n    private static MethodHandle findSpecConstructor() {\n        try {\n            MethodHandles.Lookup lookup = MethodHandles.privateLookupIn(JDKDSAPublicKey.class, MethodHandles.lookup());\n            return lookup.findConstructor(\n                    JDKDSAPublicKey.class,\n                    MethodType.methodType(void.class, DSAPublicKeySpec.class));\n        }\n        catch (IllegalAccessException | NoSuchMethodException e) {\n            throw new ExceptionInInitializerError(e);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static MethodHandle findWriteObject() {\n        try {\n            MethodHandles.Lookup lookup = MethodHandles.privateLookupIn(JDKDSAPublicKey.class, MethodHandles.lookup());\n            return lookup.findVirtual(\n                    JDKDSAPublicKey.class,\n                    \"writeObject\",\n                    MethodType.methodType(void.class, ObjectOutputStream.class));\n        }\n        catch (IllegalAccessException | NoSuchMethodException e) {\n            throw new ExceptionInInitializerError(e);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static MethodHandle findReadObject() {\n        try {\n            MethodHandles.Lookup lookup = MethodHandles.privateLookupIn(JDKDSAPublicKey.class, MethodHandles.lookup());\n            return lookup.findVirtual(\n                    JDKDSAPublicKey.class,\n                    \"readObject\",\n                    MethodType.methodType(void.class, ObjectInputStream.class));\n        }\n        catch (IllegalAccessException | NoSuchMethodException e) {\n            throw new ExceptionInInitializerError(e);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class RecordingObjectOutputStream extends ObjectOutputStream {\n        private final List<Object> objects = new ArrayList<>();\n\n        private RecordingObjectOutputStream() throws IOException {\n            super();\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected void writeObjectOverride(Object object) {\n            objects.add(object);\n        }\n\n        private List<Object> objects() {\n            return objects;\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class SequenceObjectInputStream extends ObjectInputStream {\n        private final Object[] objects;\n        private int index;\n\n        private SequenceObjectInputStream(Object... objects) throws IOException {\n            super();\n            this.objects = objects;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Object readObjectOverride() {\n            return objects[index++];\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class TrackedBigInteger extends BigInteger {\n        private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n\n        private TrackedBigInteger(long value) {\n            super(Long.toString(value));\n        }\n\n        private static TrackedBigInteger trackedValueOf(long value) {\n            return new TrackedBigInteger(value);\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}
[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating serialization codes**\n\nIt looks like existing hook tests are passing, which is good news! The `WRITE_OBJECT.invokeExact` is successfully calling `writeObject`, and I see that in the `ObjectOutputStream.writeObject`, there's no serialization metadata for BigInteger. It seems like the override path is likely not producing any metadata either, but that’s okay. I need to make sure to read `readObject` directly with `SequenceObjectInputStream` to ensure everything works as intended.\n\n**Addressing method invocation issues**\n\nI think there's a potential issue here regarding the MethodHandle invocation of the private writeObject. It doesn't seem like a natural public API, and it might not be reachable in native. Hm, that could complicate things a bit. I suppose I should consider editing a sizeable section or maybe rewrite the whole file for better clarity. Keeping that in mind will help me make the necessary adjustments.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0b73063cb9f920ab0169fc1ff423888195850cf766216ea010\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp_CAD5n2eghLKU6lWdnxk8YTDiMIhsgK80l46d7N7Tnpu7wwRCOFfnyrQYEbRx8ecJSgdiQ7Do_RYqxKjkT5j8LusJb_otKQMlbcDKa9b_TKvBkIvjMcYI25IVvW0AZrEfdNQL4JzU-m_uaHu2nQu3XhCccU1xpducgh4SEklChNf6vb_ZhIi5oS7jEiMQhbfathpqoAAQ-JFYJPtymoN7aBx_fBmn1lWBt34m8Dd5kuO6PUKHCQ9xu9ScSYc23bFHXVOHftwCBqOr91dS7SITM3WBpSEdW1gn9Hyhf7yIiIneczh_FvpBnJQQAqa0H33iZapxNKBp9gH73StZejFBrO1VfUwwCTqxxPRn8CzEgJn_4NgVPAbbpZzDQ5eGVs_J_AbWrHTbzAtqoDTTNEK_-3y9FwGVY1SCSqP9cOi3R-4KDFOL16gb5bjh548nI4whnTHqQUgfn3V9RddWurGhKdQSS7je9cK2vWXCZ3s6ibLG4mjSuLXS0ZdjlzF9gmDOI9ZrRe2BXjds_POCVXrROV79xniZT7Zezbmmc3OsLGkp7groLYD-LwBaRmh-Vee7WG5C5DOQRw_5JxOBt5jFrjPuYzWcd0E-QSr_iNdZnca1k7dhF1fTKLjkNbrBP5IYK89U8UzRdWVwN9JML0q6kMu1GhWI2WtEP6vYURclPsiCibI7hITSRFbazKHw4Ha_yFEQVHlMTO1JPAkuo-STo_uI9DzaK5sU7el1wyR5AOSZMlqPfrFu-A-5HxKxrFnSnB4cTnY23RMoNILrGIuZcIb5SnaJLP