ut bypassed the normal object serialization/deserialization machinery, so the dynamic-access call sites were still not marked covered.\n- This version uses normal object streams inside the hook invocation path, which should reach the remaining tracked call sites for the active class.\n\nI did not run compilation or tests locally, per workflow rules.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0b73063cb9f920ab0169fc214f24f88195a17678aa5b475f7d\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 642, "output": 1117, "cacheRead": 57856, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 59615, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1778131260017, "responseId": "resp_0b73063cb9f920ab0169fc213cc3ec8195bcfa63ccecabdfb3"}}
